  El Ni単o and the National Landslide Hazard Outlook for 1997-1998

    USGS and NOAA
   ___________________________________

   Summary of another Web site

   Forecast of a major El Ni単o event is causing mounting concern that 1997
   and 1998 may be years of exceptional landslide activity.

   [USGS/NOAA Haz. Outlook Map, Dec-Feb]

   The U.S. Geological Survey (USGS) has recently prepared maps of the
   National landslide hazard outlook for 1997 and 1998 by combining
   forecast information for precipitation from the National Oceanic and
   Atmospheric Administration (NOAA) with a USGS map showing landslide
   incidence and susceptibility for the conterminous United States.

   Shown above is the December-January-February National landslide hazard
   outlook.
